            "title": "Pol\u00edtica educacional em retalhos : A CAPES e a forma\u00e7\u00e3o de professores da educa\u00e7\u00e3o b\u00e1sica no Brasil",
            "abstract": [
                "Este livro \u00e9 resultado de importante estudo realizado por Nathanael da Cruz e Silva Neto sobre o papel da CAPES nas pol\u00edticas contempor\u00e2neas de forma\u00e7\u00e3o de professores da Educa\u00e7\u00e3o B\u00e1sica. Por meio de an\u00e1lise hist\u00f3rica, com aporte de ampla pesquisa bibliogr\u00e1fica e documental, o autor debru\u00e7a-se sobre as pol\u00edticas levadas a cabo por essa importante institui\u00e7\u00e3o p\u00fablica, criada em 1951, e vinculada ao Minist\u00e9rio da Educa\u00e7\u00e3o. Tradicionalmente voltada a quest\u00f5es de desenvolvimento, regula\u00e7\u00e3o e avalia\u00e7\u00e3o da p\u00f3s-gradua\u00e7\u00e3o, o texto situa e contextualiza, para o leitor, o momento exato em que a CAPES \u00e9 deslocada, tamb\u00e9m, para o epicentro da pol\u00edtica nacional de forma\u00e7\u00e3o de professores, ocupando um papel de destaque no campo da formula\u00e7\u00e3o e execu\u00e7\u00e3o das pol\u00edticas p\u00fablicas de forma\u00e7\u00e3o docente. Desse modo, no contexto do arranjo federativo brasileiro e do regime de colabora\u00e7\u00e3o, institu\u00eddo pela Constitui\u00e7\u00e3o Federal de 1988 e pela LDBEN/1996, a \u201cNova CAPES\u201d \u00e9 elevada \u00e0 condi\u00e7\u00e3o de importante agente na coordena\u00e7\u00e3o das pol\u00edticas nacionais de forma\u00e7\u00e3o inicial e continuada de nossos professores. As fragilidades e focaliza\u00e7\u00e3o das pol\u00edticas, aponta o estudo, s\u00e3o ainda o grande desafio para o avan\u00e7o dos programas e das metas de forma\u00e7\u00e3o docente. Por fim, este livro \u00e9 um convite irrecus\u00e1vel para aqueles que almejam conhecer, com riqueza de detalhes, marcos importantes da hist\u00f3ria da educa\u00e7\u00e3o e da pol\u00edtica educacional brasileira",
                "This book is the result of an important study carried out by Nathanael da Cruz e Silva Neto on the role of CAPES in contemporary policies for training Basic Education teachers. Through historical analysis, with the contribution of extensive bibliographical and documental research, the author focuses on the policies carried out by this important public institution, created in 1951, and linked to the Ministry of Education. Traditionally focused on postgraduate development, regulation and evaluation issues, the text situates and contextualizes, for the reader, the exact moment when CAPES is also shifted to the epicenter of the national teacher training policy, occupying a outstanding role in the field of formulation and execution of public policies for teacher training. Thus, in the context of the Brazilian federative arrangement and the collaboration regime, instituted by the Federal Constitution of 1988 and by LDBEN/1996, the \u201cNew CAPES\u201d is elevated to the condition of an important agent in the coordination of national policies for initial and continued training of our teachers. The weaknesses and focus of policies, points out the study, are still the great challenge for the advancement of programs and teacher training goals. Finally, this book is an irresistible invitation for those who wish to know, in great detail, important milestones in the history of education and Brazilian educational policy"
            ],
